© University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Scottish:  see  Loudon  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Loudon","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Louden  ."]}]},{"name":"James","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the name borne in the New Testament by two of Christ's disciples, James son of Zebedee and James son of Alphaeus. This form comes from Late Latin <i>Iacomus</i>, a variant of <i>Iacobus</i>, Latin form of Greek <i>Iakobos</i>. This is the same name as Old Testament   Jacob   (Hebrew <i>Yaakov</i>), but for many centuries now they have been thought of in the English-speaking world as two distinct names. In Britain, <i>James</i> is a royal name that from the beginning of the 15th century onwards was associated particularly with the Scottish house of Stewart:  James I  of Scotland (  1394–1437 ; ruled  1424–37 ) was a patron of the arts and a noted poet, as well as an energetic ruler.  King James VI  of Scotland (  1566–1625 ; reigned  1567–1625 ) succeeded to the throne of England in  1603 . His grandson,  James II  of England (  1633–1701 ; reigned  1685–8 ) was a Roman Catholic, deposed in  1688  in favour of his Protestant daughter Mary and her husband William of Orange. From then on he, his son (also called James), and his grandson Charles (‘Bonnie Prince Charlie’) made various unsuccessful attempts to recover the English throne. Their supporters were known as Jacobites (from Latin <i>Iacobus</i>), and the name James became for a while particularly associated with Roman Catholicism on the one hand, and Highland opposition to the English government on the other. Nevertheless, it has since become one of the most perennially popular boys' names."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of any of the given names beginning with the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When James de Loudoun was born in 1126, in Loudoun, Ayrshire, Scotland, his father, Lambinus de Loudoun II, was 21 and his mother, Mrs. Lambinus de Loudoun, was 21. He married Jane in 1148, in Loudoun, Ayrshire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1165, in Guelff, Habergy, Luxembourg, Belgium, at the age of 39, and was buried in Guelff, Habergy, Luxembourg, Belgium."},"et":{"1126–1165":"1126–1165","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","1169–1250":"1169–1250","1106–1150":"1106–1150","1106–Female":"1106–Surnud","1106":"1106","1126":"1126","before 1148":"1148","Abt 1150":"umbes 1150","1169":"1169","1145":"1145","1165":"1165","1130":"1130","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","Loudoun, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Loudoun, Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Guelff, Habergy, Luxembourg, Belgium":"Guelff, Habergy, Luxembourg, Belgia"},"fi":{"1126–1165":"1126–1165","1130–Female":"1130–Kuollut","1169–1250":"1169–1250","1106–1150":"1106–1150","1106–Female":"1106–Kuollut","1106":"1106","1126":"1126","before 1148":"1148","Abt 1150":"noin 1150","1169":"1169","1145":"1145","1165":"1165","1130":"1130","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","Loudoun, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Loudoun, Ayrshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Guelff, Habergy, Luxembourg, Belgium":"Guelff, Habergy, Luxembourg, Belgia"},"fr":{"1126–1165":"1126–1165","1130–Female":"1130–Décédée","1169–1250":"1169–1250","1106–1150":"1106–1150","1106–Female":"1106–Décédée","1106":"1106","1126":"1126","before 1148":"1148","Abt 1150":"environ 1150","1169":"1169","1145":"1145","1165":"1165","1130":"1130","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","Loudoun, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Loudoun, Ayrshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Scotland":"Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Guelff, Habergy, Luxembourg, Belgium":"Guelff, Habergy, Luxembourg, Belgique","lifeSummary":"Lorsque James de Loudoun est né en 1126, à Loudoun, Ayrshire, Écosse, son père, Lambinus de Loudoun II, avait 21 ans et sa mère, Mrs. Lambinus de Loudoun, avait 21 ans. Il a épousé Jane en 1148, à Loudoun, Ayrshire, Écosse. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1165, à Guelff, Habergy, Luxembourg, Belgique, à l’âge de 39 ans, et a été enterré à Guelff, Habergy, Luxembourg, Belgique."},"de":{"1126–1165":"1126–1165","1130–Female":"1130–Verstorben","1169–1250":"1169–1250","1106–1150":"1106–1150","1106–Female":"1106–Verstorben","1106":"1106","1126":"1126","before 1148":"1148","Abt 1150":"um 1150","1169":"1169","1145":"1145","1165":"1165","1130":"1130","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","Loudoun, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Loudoun, Ayrshire, Schottland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Schottland, United Kingdom","Guelff, Habergy, Luxembourg, Belgium":"Guelff, Hewerdingen, Luxemburg, Belgien","lifeSummary":"Als James de Loudoun 1126 in Loudoun, Ayrshire, Scotland geboren wurde, war sein Vater Lambinus de Loudoun II 21 und seine Mutter Mrs. Lambinus de Loudoun 21. Er hat 1148 in Loudoun, Ayrshire, Scotland Jane geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter. Er starb 1165 im Alter von 39 Jahren in Guelff, Hewerdingen, Luxemburg, Belgien und wurde in Guelff, Hewerdingen, Luxemburg, Belgien begraben."},"ht":{"1126–1165":"1126–1165","1130–Female":"1130–Desede","1169–1250":"1169–1250","1106–1150":"1106–1150","1106–Female":"1106–Desede","1106":"1106","1126":"1126","before 1148":"1148","Abt 1150":"about 1150","1169":"1169","1145":"1145","1165":"1165","1130":"1130","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","Loudoun, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Loudoun, Ayrshire, Ecosse, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Ecosse, United Kingdom","Guelff, Habergy, Luxembourg, Belgium":"Guelff, Habergy, Luxembourg, Belgique"},"hu":{"1126–1165":"1126–1165","1130–Female":"1130–elhunyt","1169–1250":"1169–1250","1106–1150":"1106–1150","1106–Female":"11